  "text": "Contrast ventriculography and coronary angiography were performed and quantified as previously described. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Anteroapical wall motion was semiquantitatively scored (3-normal, 2-mild hypokinesis, 1-severe hypokinesis, and 0 -akinesis). Segment shortening in the LAD perfusion territory was quantified with subendocardially placed piezoelectric crystals. [CITATION_3] Segment shortening (percentage) was calculated as (end-diastolic lengthϪend-systolic length)/(end-diastolic length)ϫ100.",
